ANTHRAX, BOVINE - CROATIA : (LICKO-SENJSKA) OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 21 Jun 2012
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2012; 25(25) [edited]
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=12064


Anthrax, Croatia
---------------
Information received on (and dated) 21 Jun 2012 from Dr Mirjana Matausic-Pisl, Assistant to Minister Ministry of Agriculture, Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Zagreb, Croatia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 15 Jun 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 18 Jun 2012
Report date: 21 Jun 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 21 Jun 2012
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 19 Dec 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1; Doljani, Doljani, Donji Lapac, Licko-Senjska
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jun 2012
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 6 / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the affected herd consisted of 6 cattle grazed on a pasture. 2 cattle died. The rest of the animals show no clinical signs.
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 33.33 percent / 33.33 percent / 100 percent / 33.33 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Cattle are probably infected on the pasture
Epidemiological comments: in response to the outbreak, vaccination of all susceptible animals on the location will be carried out.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination [this is at odds with a statement above. - Mod.MHJ]; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type; Croatian Veterinary Institute (CVI) (national laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 18 Jun 2012 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the map included in the OIE report at the source URL above. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Croatia can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/2Cy-.

As with previous postings the reality of the situation on the ground is not very clear. But fortunately they do report to OIE. - Mod.MHJ]
